-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_billing_events.sql
-- Deduplicate billing events to one row per subscription + event_month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_id,
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- models/intermediate/int_subscription_enriched.sql
-- Enrich subscriptions with user and company information
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status,
        u.company_id
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
        ON u.user_id = s.user_id
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    plan_id,
    started_at,
    ended_at,
    status,
    company_id
FROM source

-- models/intermediate/int_monthly_subscriptions.sql
-- Calculate subscription metrics by month with plan and company details
WITH billing_base AS (
    SELECT
        be.subscription_id,
        be.event_month,
        be.amount
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }} be
),
enriched AS (
    SELECT
        se.subscription_id,
        se.user_id,
        se.plan_id,
        se.status,
        se.company_id,
        b.event_month,
        b.amount,
        COALESCE(pl.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(co.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry
    FROM billing_base b
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_subscription_enriched') }} se
        ON se.subscription_id = b.subscription_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} pl
        ON pl.plan_id = se.plan_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} co
        ON co.company_id = se.company_id
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    tier,
    industry
FROM enriched
```

-- models/mart/fct_monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
-- Final fact table: monthly subscription metrics by tier and industry
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_month,
        tier,
        industry,
        subscription_id,
        user_id,
        amount
    FROM {{ ref('int_monthly_subscriptions') }}
)
SELECT
    source.event_month AS month,
    source.tier,
    source.industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT source.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(source.amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT source.user_id) AS unique_users
FROM source
GROUP BY
    source.event_month,
    source.tier,
    source.industry
ORDER BY
    source.event_month ASC,
    source.tier ASC,
    source.industry ASC
